name: Flexible Housing | CoLiving | 1A
neighborhood_overview: Fort Hill is a quiet neighborhood, perfect for long-term stays. There is a combination of families, medical professionals, and graduate students that coincide with a wonderful local history to build a strong culture in the local area. 139 Marcella is located in Highland Park within walking distance of the vibrant South End. The Jackson Square T-Stop is a 7 min walk and the Columbus Ave & Centre Street MBTA Bus Line (#22) is a 5 min walk. Within 20 min you can be in downtown Boston.
description:
If you are looking for flexibility, ease and affordability with all the uncertainty of COVID this Fall and Winter then look no further.

Thatch's Co-Living and furnished monthly rentals are tailor-made for this. Why commit to a 1 year lease, pay to move, pay a broker, buy furniture and spend precious time moving and getting settled if you aren't sure whether you'll be here for a year or not?

With Thatch you pick the perfect place and commit only to the dates you need. Let us do the rest!

The space
This is a brand new building, designed for Co-Living. All amenities, as well as utilities are included in monthly rent.

Each bedroom has a private, en-suite bathroom

In total there are five bedrooms (each with a private lock), along with a shared kitchen and living room, all of which are fully outfitted and furnished.

Washer and Dryer are in unit.

description:
If you are looking for flexibility, ease and affordability with all the uncertainty of COVID-19 this Fall and Winter then look no further. Thatch Co-Living and furnished rentals are tailor-made for your current situation.

Why commit to a 1-year lease, pay to move, pay a broker fee, buy furniture and spend precious time moving on September 1st and getting settled if you are not sure whether you will be here for a year or not? You pick the place and you pick the dates, we provide the housing.

The space
This is a brand new apartment, designed for Co-Living. All amenities, as well as utilities are included in rent.

There are four bedrooms (each with a private lock), with a shared kitchen and living room. Thatch provides bi-weekly common cleaning, and offers private room cleaning upon request. Each unit is fully furnished with a Tuft & Needle Mattress, and security is provided by Latch.
